Xref: msuinfo sci.crypt:16323 alt.privacy.clipper:332

>     7.   The chips can be programmed to not enter secure mode if
>          the LEF field has been tampered with (e.g., modified,
>          superencrypted, replaced);

I'd like some clarification on "not enter secure mode".  I notice
it's *not* worded "not synchronize".  Does that mean it will still
communicate, but not encode the data stream?  If so, I sure hope
it informs the users of the communication devices -- otherwise
an eavesdropper only has to fiddle with the LEF to change the
data stream to plaintext.
